long_desc.thetext:
@SuppressWarnings("null")
public class NullWarn {

    // Some code

}

gets two Warnings (not in scope of any package default):
line 1: Unnecessary @SuppressWarnings("null")
line 2: A default nullness annotation has not been specified for the type NullWarn

The @SuppressWarnings was generated from a quickfix on the other warning. Using the same quickfix again will create:
@SuppressWarnings({"null", "null", "null", "null", "null", "null"})

Each tagged with jet another warning ...

Tested with:
eclipse-SDK-N20140730-2000-linux-gtk-x86_64.tar.gz and
eclipse-SDK-I20140805-0800-linux-gtk-x86_64.tar.gz
